<div ID=towncountryregion class='bodysansserif towncountryregion'>Santo Domingo in&nbsp;Tepoztlán, Morelos, Mexico &#8212; <i>The&nbsp;Central&nbsp;Highlands (North&nbsp;America)</i></div><tr><td valign=top colspan=2 class=bodysansserif><fieldset><legend><font color=red>A Private Note from Editor to the Contributor of this Page</font><br></legend>¡Qué bien! It is always a pleasure to have more markers from Mexico! - Makali Bruton, regional editor 4.27.24<br><small>This note is shown only on the contributor's copy of this page</small></fieldset></td></tr><div class=shim6pt>&nbsp;</div><h1>Coyulan (Lugar de Coyotes)</h1><h2 style='margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: 8px;'><i>Coyulan (Place of coyotes)</i></h2><div class=shim12pt>&nbsp;</div><div class=shim12pt>&nbsp;</div><div style='all:initial;margin-left:0px;'><div class=photoright><div style='max-width:400px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;'><a target=_blank href='PhotoFullSize.asp?PhotoID=786030'><img loading=lazy class=photoimage src=Photos7/786/Photo786030.jpg?425202415800PM style='max-height:225px;' alt='Coyulan (Lugar de Coyotes) Marker image. Click for full size.' title='Coyulan (Lugar de Coyotes) Marker. Click for full size.'></a><div class=imagecredit>Photographed By Christopher Athanas,  March 31, 2024</div> <!-- imagecredit --> <div class=imagecaption>1. Coyulan (Lugar de Coyotes) Marker</div></div></div></div><span class=sectionhead>Inscription. </span><div id=inscription1 style='display:none;'><i>English translation</i> , Zapatista House-Barracks of <b>General Leobardo Galván González</b> , The only person from Morelos who participated from the beginning in the work of the "Sovereign Revolutionary Convention" in Aguascalientes (1914-1916).</b> ,   ,  He was born in this house in 1879 and died in combat in San Pedro Actopan, Milpa Alta, D.F. on March 21, 1917. ,   ,  Honorable City Council of Tepoztlán, Morelos, November 20, 2014 . This historical marker  was erected  in 2014 by Honorable Ayuntamiento de Tepoztlán, Morelos. It  is in Santo Domingo in Tepoztlán Morelos Mexico</div>
